generif.text: cloning and characterization of RPK118 as a sphingosine kinase-1-binding protein
Identified as a pseudokinase and named RSKL1

findings indicate that RPK118 is a PRDX3-binding protein that may be involved in transporting PRDX3 from the cytoplasm to its mitochondrial site of function or to other membrane structures via endosome trafficking.

interpro.desc: Ribosomal protein S6 kinase delta-1, PX domain

name: ribosomal protein S6 kinase C1
other_names: ribosomal S6 kinase-like protein with two PSK domains 118 kDa protein
summary: Sphingosine kinase catalyzes the formation of sphingosine 1 phosphate, a lipid cellular messenger. The protein encoded by this gene can bind to sphingosine kinase and to phosphatidylinositol 3-phosphate, suggesting a role in sphingosine 1 phophate signaling. The encoded protein can also bind to peroxiredoxin-3 and may help transport it to mitochondria. [provided by RefSeq, Mar 2017].
